Reasoning: The paper discusses the problem of consistency in distributed systems, which is a common topic in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of key-value stores and graph applications suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The focus on system design and the proposed approach for handling weaker consistency models suggests that the paper may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the discussion of detecting violations and ensuring correctness suggests that the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
